        <body>
        <div type="letter">
        <opener><dateline><date when="1917-10-04">October 04, 1917.<dateline></date><salute>My dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet</persName>:-</salute>
        </opener>
            <p>         
             Thank you very much for your letter and your statement. I am delighted to know that you have already got so much money, and I do hope you will get the whole amount. It is a little painful to observe that you paid less for the poems and articles in your <title key="poetry" level="j">magazine</title> than you did for the printing. So are the arts appreciated in a great industrial democracy. Your office force  at the present time is certainly eclectic.</p>
             <!-- Added the landlady of the WHinton Inn to the possible additions -->
           <p> By the way, please send me the proofs of <title key="landladyOfTheWhintonInn">“The Landlady of the Whinton Inn.”</title> You are to print it in November, you remember. I hope to get my review of <persName key="louis_untermeyer">Louis Untermeyer</persName>’s <title key="theseTimes">“These Times”</title> off to you next week without fail.             
            </p>
              <closure>Affectionately yours,</closure>
            </div>
        </body>
